Staple FPS experience.

CS:GO Is probably one of the most basic shooters out there, and that not inheretly a bad thing. Down to its core, this game is flawless. Everything tought out and its constantly updated.

Learning Counter Strike... You can probably get on an intermediate level in a simple afternoon. The goal of the game is extremely simple, easy to learn, hard to master, similar to Valves other FPS, TF2.

You go in, you either plant the bomb or make sure the bomb is not planted. You shoot the enemy team, it really is that simple.

One of the main things that I've noticed with this game, its that your performance is never the same. Sometimes you could be carrying your team, eliminating the enemy team with deadly precision, yet other times you cant even hit someone with a Negev who is 2 meters in front of you, thus resulting in a humiliating death. Your teams attitude towards the game can also hinder your perfomance. Even if "Даниил [insert gambling site]" is begging to be kicked after the first round cause the 10 year old veteran player missed his AWP shot on the last enemy player, that could really get on peoples nerve. 

The game is awesome, DEFINETLY give it a go or two to see if it hooks you. Just make sure you nab a friend or two to play with.  The community could use a little work, and I'm not talking about the external one, but the internal one. I have a feeling most of the people who I've played with are below the age of 9 and their gamesense is absolutely trash, but thats just another thing that comes with this game.

9/10
